ast time was when my grandfather died.</p><p>Then an angel arrives.</p><p>A family friend approaches mum. \"Your daughter looks unwell. She is losing her hair. What is the matter?\" My mother, at her wits end, tells the woman the truth. \"George,\" the angel says. \"Tell her to go to George.\"</p><p>George is a small town in South Africa. I learn there is a clinic that specializes in treating severe skin disease. I adamantly refuse. I have had enough of doctors, hospitals, foul smelling topical creams and hopes dashed. Mum convinces me.</p><p>In a week, I find myself there against my wishes. I withstand the indignity, once again, of being naked, the grotesque lesions under neon light, and I listen to the shocked gasps of the doctors and nurses.</p><p>\"We\'ve never seen it this bad,\" one says in the tiny examination room.</p><p>I glance dully outside the window of my room to see a blue lake and a blue sky amid green trees and grass. Postcard perfect. I count the hours.</p><p>Who could imagine where I am? I am a celebrity in Nairobi, making it big.</p><p>\"What do you do?\" I am asked.</p><p>\"Nothing,\" I respond curtly to any one who dares make conversation with me. I certainly don\'t want to start a conversation about being on television or hosting a radio show for that matter. What would my viewers on KTN and listeners on Capital FM Radio think of me?</p><p>Mind, body and spirit are the focus at this clinic. It sounds insane to me. I am told to do mediation, deep relaxation and creative visualization three times a day. I lie on the floor listening to the voice in charge.</p><p>\"Every day in every way I am getting better and better. I have no desire to eat the foods I know are bad for me...\" I brainwash myself. It works.</p><p>I eat yogurt or bran for breakfast, salads or fish for lunch and chicken for dinner. Nothing tastes good. I yearn for Tabasco. I drink only herbal tea and torrents of water.</p><p>I write a long letter to my psoriasis, describing how it causes me pain, how it hurts my relationships, how it makes me weak. I blame it for not allowing me to be free. I blame it for my rage, my violence, my bullying and my inability to feel loved, for my need for praise and constant reassurance.</p><p>I berate and belittle it. I coax and cajole it. I remind it of my sexless life. I beg and plead for it to go away. Then I thank my psoriasis. It has taught me to have no vanity, more compassion and to withhold judgment.</p><p>I am crying, emotionally drained, and hot underneath my long sleeves and jeans. I take a shovel, pick a spot outside and dig deep. I place the pages into the hole. I plant a tree. I use my hands to touch the earth. Nature seems surprisingly reassuring.</p><p>In this instance, I bury my past. I have said everything I needed to say to my skin. The tree will give life, oxygen. Perhaps it will give me a chance to breathe again.</p><p>A breakthrough.</p><p>It has been two weeks, and I see something no one else can see -- a tiny shift. In the center of one thick plaque, there is a slight thinning. I can discern this little dent only because I have been touching my skin.</p><p>This small success galvanizes me to stick rigidly to the tough diet I have promised to undertake.</p><p>I am ecstatic, fully of new energy. My smile is real. I am positive.</p><p>I return to Nairobi with a new mindset, a sense of control. I maintain the regimen like a military staff sergeant.</p><p>Every 28 days, I see progress. It is small. But it is there. The months pass. The smell stops. The centers of the lesions disappear like small mountains collapsing on themselves. They turn from red to pink to white.</p><p>I watch with fascination the metamorphosis of my skin. The continents on my body move apart with the seismic change in my mind. The scales no longer build. Then they are gone. I can\'t believe it.</p><p>It has been six months. I am clear. I am in remission. I have no scales. I am normal. I am finally free.</p><p>And there is no medication. Only food. \"Let food be thy medicine and medicine be thy food.\"</p><p>When I walk triumphantly into my dermatologist\'s office, she is startled. I healed myself with the power of my mind, I announce. She is shocked. She later tells me she believes there is a place for natural healing in medicine.</p><p>I can\'t say what will work for others, but I believe that diet, mindset and a wonderful support system were the best long-term answers for me. There is a place for light therapy or steroid cream or biological medication, but back then I healed myself from the inside out.</p><p>After my transformation, my family takes me to Mombasa, on the Kenyan coast. I don\'t dread it for the first time in my life.</p><p>I have a new bikini, dark blue with a yellow rim. I have never worn one. It is so soft. It feels feminine. I have never felt like a woman the way I do when I put it on. I see all my curves in a different light.</p><p>The mirror is not my enemy any longer.</p>','/content/images/2015/05/magcover.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<span style=\"color: rgb(77, 77, 77); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(237, 239, 240);\">I have spent more than a decade of my professional career on international television, my face visible to millions each day. Yet I have spent a lifetime hiding.</span>',3,'2015-05-09 19:01:24',2,'2015-06-05 03:41:15',2,'2015-05-09 19:22:00',2,0),(14,'b57dae14-17da-463b-98aa-ca951ed934d8','The Meeting','the-meeting','<p>I glance down at the paper in my hand and stare in shock.</p><p>â€œSonofabitch!â€ I yell, scaring a tiny freshman that happened to be walking right by me.</p><p>â€œSorry! I wasnâ€™t talking about you! Iâ€™m sure your mom is very pleasant!â€ I call after them but theyâ€™ve already scampered down the hall, probably to the safety of the freshman hall.</p><p>Someone in the office must be playing around with me, because they paired me up with the smartest and most science obsessed kid in the entire school. I was just looking for a nerd that I could charm with a smile and a low-cut top here in there to give me all the answers to my next Chem test.</p><p>JP Carlson was definitely NOT going to be that person for me. Although I had never really talked to JP, he has a reputation of being a pompous know-it-all that was also positively incorruptible . Apparently, one conversation with him will leave you feeling like a stupid monkey that hasnâ€™t been blessed by evolutionâ€”his words, not mine. This kid would take one look at my Chemistry grade and laugh me all the way to summer schoolâ€”or worse a 5th year of high school. I quickly turned back to the office and marched to the front desk.</p><p>â€œExcuse me,â€ I said to the girl sitting at the desk, â€œI think there has been some kind of mistake.â€ I handed her my paper and she glanced it over. â€œThere is no mistake,â€ she said and returned my paper, â€œJP is the tutor that covers all junior science cases.â€ Cases? What the hell? Iâ€™m not a junkie or something! Iâ€™m just a dummy that canâ€™t grasp the fundamentals of Chemistry! â€œUmâ€¦ok then. Sorry.â€ I replied, took my paper, and left the office. Guess I really am going to have to be humiliated in front of the smartest kid in all South Carolina.</p><p>I warily made my way to the library secretly hoping JP was too busy working on the next nuclear reactor or some shit to bother tutoring me.</p><p>No such luck.</p><p>He was sitting at one of the round tables near the windows with piles of chemistry books surrounding him, looking at the books like they were Legoâ€™s and he was a three-year old kid that couldnâ€™t wait to play with them.</p><p>â€œWhatâ€¦aâ€¦WEIRDOâ€ I muttered and plastered a fake smile on my face as I walked up to him.</p><p>â€œHi JP, Iâ€™m Charlie.â€</p><p>He looked up at me and flashed the most beautiful smile I have ever seen on any human being that isnâ€™t Ryan Gosling. I looked at him closely then realized that Mr. Supernerd is actually a Superhottie!</p><p>â€œHi Charlie,â€ he said, the beautiful smile still on his face, â€œyouâ€™re ten minutes late.â€ Needles to say that winning smile disappeared in a heart beat and it was kind of sad to see if go.</p><p>He motioned to the seat next to him and I plopped down rolling my eyes. I was tempted tell him I didnâ€™t want him to tutor me and was desperately trying to get rid of him, but decided against it. Itâ€™s bad enough that the nerd/hottie has to help me with chemistry and that he thinks I donâ€™t have the mental capacity to tell time. No point adding, â€˜rude bitchâ€™ to the laundry list of my apparent flaws.</p><p>â€œSo why are you here Charlie?â€ he asked after I finally pulled all my stuff from my bag.</p><p>Is this kid serious? I clearly need help in Chemistry.</p><p>â€œWellâ€¦umâ€¦I suck at Chemistry and would really prefer to graduate with the rest of the kids my age. So I need help,â€ I said trying to hide the irritation in my voice.</p><p>â€œWell thatâ€™s excellent!â€ He exclaimed adjusting his glasses (which totally hid these gorgeous grey eyes), â€œYou are motivated and willing to take the initiative to improve your grade and your study skills.â€ I stared at him in disbelief.</p><p>Seriously kid, who are you? Motivation? Initiative? You sound like one of those inspirational posters they hang in the counseling office.</p><p>â€œYea sure whatever,â€ I said tapping my pencil anxiously, â€œCan we get started? I have to meet up with my friends in an hour.â€</p><p>â€œFriends can wait, Charlie. However, your performance in your chemistry class cannot afford to be ignored any longer. This tutoring session cannot wait.â€ JP said quietly.</p><p>Ok, I donâ€™t care how hot this kid might be, he is really getting on my nerves. So I decided to get back at him at bit.</p><p>â€œJP, lemme ask you something.â€</p><p>â€œYes?â€ he asked, probably assuming I was going to ask him about photosynthesis or some sciencey shit like that.</p><p>â€œWhat do you do for fun? Like real fun, besides building models of atoms or stuff like that?â€ I asked.</p><p>â€œThat question is irrelevant to this study session. If you want to ask me something about chemistry then I have an answer for you.â€ He retorted.</p><p>â€œIt was just a simple questionâ€ I muttered flipping through my chemistry bookâ€”it looked like gibberish to me.</p><p>â€œOk,â€ he said, â€œWell I have a simple question for you.â€</p><p>â€œGo ahead. Iâ€™m an open book. Pun intendedâ€ I replied glibly, motioning to the open book in front of me.</p><p>I could tell he wanted to laugh at my cheesy joke but decided to say â€œprofessionalâ€</p><p>â€œWhy are you really here? I looked at you transcript and chemistry is not the only class you are struggling in. Youâ€™ve pulled up your other grades from earlier this semester, but something doesnâ€™t make sense. You were a fairly good student before Christmas break and all of a sudden your grades plummet. What happened over Christmas break?â€ he asked.</p><p>Oh I donâ€™t knowâ€¦lets think. Well first I lied to my best friends, nearly got them arrested and all of that just to lose the love of my life to my childhood arch nemesis. Nopeâ€¦nothing of significance that would cause my grades to fall. But there is no way in hell Iâ€™m telling Mr. Smarty Pants all that though.</p><p>â€œLook, itâ€™s really cute that you care and everything,â€ I said slamming my book closed and standing up, â€œBut I did not sign up for a counseling session. So if you want to go all Oprah circa 2004 on me, I can leave.â€</p><p>â€œCharlie sit down,â€ JP said, standing up as well. â€œI didnâ€™t mean to upset you. You obviously donâ€™t want to talk about it so letâ€™s just keep this professional and leave the personal questions outside of the tutoring sessions? OK?â€</p><p>Outside of tutoring sessions? Does he think weâ€™re going to become besties and talk about our life problems? I think not.</p><p>â€œFineâ€¦â€I muttered. â€œBut the only reason Iâ€™m staying is because being on the five-year plan is really not a good look for anyone.â€</p>','<p>I glance down at the paper in my hand and stare in shock.</p><p>â€œSonofabitch!â€ I yell, scaring a tiny freshman that happened to be walking right by me.</p><p>â€œSorry! I wasnâ€™t talking about you! Iâ€™m sure your mom is very pleasant!â€ I call after them but theyâ€™ve already scampered down the hall, probably to the safety of the freshman hall.</p><p>Someone in the office must be playing around with me, because they paired me up with the smartest and most science obsessed kid in the entire school. I was just looking for a nerd that I could charm with a smile and a low-cut top here in there to give me all the answers to my next Chem test.</p><p>JP Carlson was definitely NOT going to be that person for me. Although I had never really talked to JP, he has a reputation of being a pompous know-it-all that was also positively incorruptible . Apparently, one conversation with him will leave you feeling like a stupid monkey that hasnâ€™t been blessed by evolutionâ€”his words, not mine. This kid would take one look at my Chemistry grade and laugh me all the way to summer schoolâ€”or worse a 5th year of high school. I quickly turned back to the office and marched to the front desk.</p><p>â€œExcuse me,â€ I said to the girl sitting at the desk, â€œI think there has been some kind of mistake.â€ I handed her my paper and she glanced it over. â€œThere is no mistake,â€ she said and returned my paper, â€œJP is the tutor that covers all junior science cases.â€ Cases? What the hell? Iâ€™m not a junkie or something! Iâ€™m just a dummy that canâ€™t grasp the fundamentals of Chemistry! â€œUmâ€¦ok then. Sorry.â€ I replied, took my paper, and left the office. Guess I really am going to have to be humiliated in front of the smartest kid in all South Carolina.</p><p>I warily made my way to the library secretly hoping JP was too busy working on the next nuclear reactor or some shit to bother tutoring me.</p><p>No such luck.</p><p>He was sitting at one of the round tables near the windows with piles of chemistry books surrounding him, looking at the books like they were Legoâ€™s and he was a three-year old kid that couldnâ€™t wait to play with them.</p><p>â€œWhatâ€¦aâ€¦WEIRDOâ€ I muttered and plastered a fake smile on my face as I walked up to him.</p><p>â€œHi JP, Iâ€™m Charlie.â€</p><p>He looked up at me and flashed the most beautiful smile I have ever seen on any human being that isnâ€™t Ryan Gosling. I looked at him closely then realized that Mr. Supernerd is actually a Superhottie!</p><p>â€œHi Charlie,â€ he said, the beautiful smile still on his face, â€œyouâ€™re ten minutes late.â€ Needles to say that winning smile disappeared in a heart beat and it was kind of sad to see if go.</p><p>He motioned to the seat next to him and I plopped down rolling my eyes. I was tempted tell him I didnâ€™t want him to tutor me and was desperately trying to get rid of him, but decided against it. Itâ€™s bad enough that the nerd/hottie has to help me with chemistry and that he thinks I donâ€™t have the mental capacity to tell time. No point adding, â€˜rude bitchâ€™ to the laundry list of my apparent flaws.</p><p>â€œSo why are you here Charlie?â€ he asked after I finally pulled all my stuff from my bag.</p><p>Is this kid serious? I clearly need help in Chemistry.</p><p>â€œWellâ€¦umâ€¦I suck at Chemistry and would really prefer to graduate with the rest of the kids my age. So I need help,â€ I said trying to hide the irritation in my voice.</p><p>â€œWell thatâ€™s excellent!â€ He exclaimed adjusting his glasses (which totally hid these gorgeous grey eyes), â€œYou are motivated and willing to take the initiative to improve your grade and your study skills.â€ I stared at him in disbelief.</p><p>Seriously kid, who are you? Motivation? Initiative? You sound like one of those inspirational posters they hang in the counseling office.</p><p>â€œYea sure whatever,â€ I said tapping my pencil anxiously, â€œCan we get started? I have to meet up with my friends in an hour.â€</p><p>â€œFriends can wait, Charlie. However, your performance in your chemistry class cannot afford to be ignored any longer. This tutoring session cannot wait.â€ JP said quietly.</p><p>Ok, I donâ€™t care how hot this kid might be, he is really getting on my nerves. So I decided to get back at him at bit.</p><p>â€œJP, lemme ask you something.â€</p><p>â€œYes?â€ he asked, probably assuming I was going to ask him about photosynthesis or some sciencey shit like that.</p><p>â€œWhat do you do for fun? Like real fun, besides building models of atoms or stuff like that?â€ I asked.</p><p>â€œThat question is irrelevant to this study session. If you want to ask me something about chemistry then I have an answer for you.â€ He retorted.</p><p>â€œIt was just a simple questionâ€ I muttered flipping through my chemistry bookâ€”it looked like gibberish to me.</p><p>â€œOk,â€ he said, â€œWell I have a simple question for you.â€</p><p>â€œGo ahead. Iâ€™m an open book. Pun intendedâ€ I replied glibly, motioning to the open book in front of me.</p><p>I could tell he wanted to laugh at my cheesy joke but decided to say â€œprofessionalâ€</p><p>â€œWhy are you really here? I looked at you transcript and chemistry is not the only class you are struggling in. Youâ€™ve pulled up your other grades from earlier this semester, but something doesnâ€™t make sense. You were a fairly good student before Christmas break and all of a sudden your grades plummet. What happened over Christmas break?â€ he asked.</p><p>Oh I donâ€™t knowâ€¦lets think. Well first I lied to my best friends, nearly got them arrested and all of that just to lose the love of my life to my childhood arch nemesis. Nopeâ€¦nothing of significance that would cause my grades to fall. But there is no way in hell Iâ€™m telling Mr. Smarty Pants all that though.</p><p>â€œLook, itâ€™s really cute that you care and everything,â€ I said slamming my book closed and standing up, â€œBut I did not sign up for a counseling session. So if you want to go all Oprah circa 2004 on me, I can leave.â€</p><p>â€œCharlie sit down,â€ JP said, standing up as well. â€œI didnâ€™t mean to upset you. You obviously donâ€™t want to talk about it so letâ€™s just keep this professional and leave the personal questions outside of the tutoring sessions? OK?â€</p><p>Outside of tutoring sessions? Does he think weâ€™re going to become besties and talk about our life problems? I think not.</p><p>â€œFineâ€¦â€I muttered. â€œBut the only reason Iâ€™m staying is because being on the five-year plan is really not a good look for anyone.â€</p>','/content/images/2015/05/chemistry.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n                            &nbsp;First portion of a chapter of a young-adult novel I\'ve been writing for years.\n                        ',5,'2015-05-09 19:24:04',2,'2015-05-13 01:54:58',2,'2015-05-09 19:24:20',1,0),(18,'e199fdb3-aeb1-4064-ab17-ef9ede14a69d','This is a test','this-is-a-test','<p><b>So...things are about to take off with aKoma. <i>Gentlewomen, gentlemen</i>...START YOUR ENGINES!!!</b></p>','<p><b>So...things are about to take off with aKoma. <i>Gentlewomen, gentlemen</i>...START YOUR ENGINES!!!</b></p>',NULL,0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'2015-05-13 12:10:33',8,'2015-05-13 12:10:33',8,'2015-05-13 12:10:33',8,0),(19,'84b6a2a1-1368-416e-80c6-32ab75bfd3da','Travelouges','travelouges-2','<p>Start writing your story here...</p>','<p>Start writing your story here...</p>','/content/images/2015/05/vintage-suitcase-table-via-texas_inetgiant.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n                            I\'ve always wanted to travel the world and be able to see as many countries as possible. If I ever win a million dollars (hopefully more), I would go on a world wind tour of the following countries and cites...',5,'2015-05-13 17:32:18',5,'2015-06-05 03:41:14',2,'2015-05-13 17:33:37',5,0),(20,'9c650140-1da7-47ca-b614-ff3f6b081731','Dogs are the best','dogs-are-the-best','<p>We <b>love</b> dogs. This is<i> Luka</i>. He likes going to the park and sniffing other dog\'s butts.&nbsp;</p><h2>This is a test for headline subtitle.&nbsp;</h2><p>We are still writing and writing and writing and testing and hoping that this will all work smoothly. Anyway, thanks for looking at the picture and joining us with this test. I want to tell you that the restaurant called 15 East is <b>excellent</b>, by the way.&nbsp;</p><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p><br></p>','<p>We <b>love</b> dogs. This is<i> Luka</i>. He likes going to the park and sniffing other dog\'s butts.&nbsp;</p><h2>This is a test for headline subtitle.&nbsp;</h2><p>We are still writing and writing and writing and testing and hoping that this will all work smoothly. Anyway, thanks for looking at the picture and joining us with this test. I want to tell you that the restaurant called 15 East is <b>excellent</b>, by the way.&nbsp;</p><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p><br></p>','/content/images/2015/05/zain_luka.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n                            We love dogs. This is Luka. He likes going to the park and sniffing other dog\'s butts.&nbsp;This is a test for headline subtitle.&nbsp;',5,'2015-05-13 20:45:04',5,'2015-06-05 03:41:14',2,'2015-05-13 20:45:04',5,0),(21,'79d77828-c3e2-4bc9-872b-f3f54a4a44ce','This little piggy','this-little-piggy','<p>i am a piggy. &nbsp; i eat and eat and eat until i feel sick. &nbsp;then i poo and poo and poo. &nbsp; momma is a dummy. she &nbsp;just feeds me each time i look miserable and heartbroken. &nbsp;frankly she is a sucker. &nbsp; i know i can get anything i want with my cute sad eyes. &nbsp;take that bitches!</p>','<p>i am a piggy. &nbsp; i eat and eat and eat until i feel sick. &nbsp;then i poo and poo and poo. &nbsp; momma is a dummy. she &nbsp;just feeds me each time i look miserable and heartbroken. &nbsp;frankly she is a sucker. &nbsp; i know i can get anything i want with my cute sad eyes. &nbsp;take that bitches!</p>','/content/images/2015/05/sad-eyes-luka.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'2015-05-13 20:54:36',3,'2015-06-05 03:41:14',2,'2015-05-13 20:54:36',3,0),(22,'e8305748-10b9-4ac3-a603-65fbfb12c57a','We are now testing save a story.','we-are-now-testing-save-a-story-2','<p>This is a picture I took of Meryl Streep talking at a dinner. It\'s super creepy but she\'s an ethereal angel and is my inspiration for life. All Hail Meryl.</p>','<p>This is a picture I took of Meryl Streep talking at a dinner. It\'s super creepy but she\'s an ethereal angel and is my inspiration for life. All Hail Meryl.</p>','/content/images/2015/05/MERYL.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,'2015-05-13 20:59:57',5,'2015-06-05 01:34:59',2,'2015-05-26 12:19:26',5,0),(24,'cb534ce9-fb98-4ba3-b71e-d7b1dbaa1931','This is a test again on mobile','this-is-a-test-again-on-mobile','<p>Start&nbsp;</p>','<p>Start&nbsp;</p>','/content/images/2015/05/image.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'2015-05-14 00:22:13',3,'2015-06-05 03:41:14',2,'2015-05-14 00:22:13',3,0),(25,'6b1613d5-15cf-4424-82cc-fd72e25becc6','Another test from The Chidi','another-test-from-the-chidi','<p>This is being done in chrome. Desktop. SO, the font in the story mode is off. But that will be fixed of course. Would like to add a link...have that in the bubble. Still think being able to center justify should be an option also.&nbsp;</p><p>What about previewing this story when I am done? Hmmm.&nbsp;</p><p>I also think giving our writers the ability to embed images from Getty would be a game changer. Don\'t you think? Yes? I thought so.</p><p>:-)</p><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>Ah, I see the double enter thing gives you a nice border line thingamajig. Cool.</p><p>Alright, let\'s test this mother.</p><p>C</p>','<p>This is being done in chrome. Desktop. SO, the font in the story mode is off. But that will be fixed of course. Would like to add a link...have that in the bubble. Still think being able to center justify should be an option also.&nbsp;</p><p>What about previewing this story when I am done? Hmmm.&nbsp;</p><p>I also think giving our writers the ability to embed images from Getty would be a game changer. Don\'t you think? Yes? I thought so.</p><p>:-)</p><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>Ah, I see the double enter thing gives you a nice border line thingamajig. Cool.</p><p>Alright, let\'s test this mother.</p><p>C</p>',NULL,0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'2015-05-14 12:31:55',8,'2015-06-05 01:34:59',2,'2015-05-14 12:32:10',8,0),(26,'ec213d19-91c2-4eaa-9b70-f7f454cd2d82','Alright, Let\'s Test This Mother Again (editor)','alright-lets-test-this-mother-again-editor-2','<h2>What are we testing here?</h2><!----><p><b>The editor:</b> looks like we are now able to just click on the \"enter your title\" and \"enter you body text\" and get cracking with those two disappearing. Good. Awesome. Don\'t like the blue box thingamajig that appears though. That\'s got to go.</p><p><b>Carriage/Enter: </b>One \"enter\" seems to give a double space. Hmmm...that may or may not be ok. Two \"enters\" gives you a line break. We should disable that. Not sure writers will like that.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Text Styler: </b>I see the link and quotes pieces are in. Nice. Let me put a link in the here. Nope, that didn\'t work. Grrr. What about a quote...let\'s see. I am The Chidi</p><p>Whoops. It indents and bolds the entire paragraph and everything underneath the highlighted text, not the text I highlighted.&nbsp;</p><p>BUG!! (as in the way cops or soldiers yell, \"GUN!!\"&nbsp;</p><p>It should indent and italicize the text selected, no? No. Seems it should be the entire paragraph. Ok...cool.&nbsp;</p><p>False alarm on the selection piece. But we should italicize.&nbsp;</p><p>What else?&nbsp;</p><p><b>Image: </b>Whoa, mama. That is one big ass image. Will it crop out? We shall see. Also, anyway to remove the image place holder thing and just use a small camera icon or something cleaner and funner?&nbsp;</p><p>Ha. He said \"funner\"</p><p>And yeah, why is the first line auto H3? Let\'s figure that out.&nbsp;</p><p>Alright...done for now.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Tested on:</b></p><p>Device: Desktop</p><p>Browser: Chrome (incognito)</p><p><b>Update</b></p><p>Hit finish, and the preview was all text mashed together, no image. Probably should not show that text in the screen after you hit publish. Definitely will disorient the writer.&nbsp;</p>','<p><h2>What are we testing here?</h2><!----><p><b>The editor:</b> looks like we are now able to just click on the \"enter your title\" and \"enter you body text\" and get cracking with those two disappearing. Good. Awesome. Don\'t like the blue box thingamajig that appears though. That\'s got to go.</p><p><b>Carriage/Enter: </b>One \"enter\" seems to give a double space. Hmmm...that may or may not be ok. Two \"enters\" gives you a line break. We should disable that. Not sure writers will like that.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Text Styler: </b>I see the link and quotes pieces are in. Nice. Let me put a link in the here. Nope, that didn\'t work. Grrr. What about a quote...let\'s see. I am The Chidi</p><p>Whoops. It indents and bolds the entire paragraph and everything underneath the highlighted text, not the text I highlighted.&nbsp;</p><p>BUG!! (as in the way cops or soldiers yell, \"GUN!!\"&nbsp;</p><p>It should indent and italicize the text selected, no? No. Seems it should be the entire paragraph. Ok...cool.&nbsp;</p><p>False alarm on the selection piece. But we should italicize.&nbsp;</p><p>What else?&nbsp;</p><p><b>Image: </b>Whoa, mama. That is one big ass image. Will it crop out? We shall see. Also, anyway to remove the image place holder thing and just use a small camera icon or something cleaner and funner?&nbsp;</p><p>Ha. He said \"funner\"</p><p>And yeah, why is the first line auto H3? Let\'s figure that out.&nbsp;</p><p>Alright...done for now.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Tested on:</b></p><p>Device: Desktop</p><p>Browser: Chrome (incognito)</p><p><b>Update</b></p><p>Hit finish, and the preview was all text mashed together, no image. Probably should not show that text in the screen after you hit publish. Definitely will disorient the writer.&nbsp;</p></p>','/content/images/2015/05/GA_3.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n                            What are we testing here?The editor: looks like we are now able to just click on the \"enter your title\" and \"enter you body text\" and get cracking with those two disappearing. Good. Awesome. Don\'t like the blue box thingamajig that appears though.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Helvetica, Arial, san-serif; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 16px;\">&nbsp;That\'s got to go.Carriage/Enter: One \"enter\" seems to give a double space. Hmmm...that may or may not be ok. Two \"enters\" gives you a line break. We should disable that. Not sure writers will like that.&nbsp;Text Styler: I see the link and quotes pieces are in. Nice. Let me put a link in the here. Nope, that didn\'t work. Grrr. What about a quote...let\'s see. I am The ChidiWhoops. It indents and bolds the entire paragraph and everything underneath the highlighted text, not the text I highlighted.&nbsp;BUG!! (as in the way cops or soldiers yell, \"GUN!!\"&nbsp;It should indent and italicize the text selected, no? No. Seems it should be the entire paragraph. Ok...cool.&nbsp;False alarm on the selection piece. But we should italicize.&nbsp;What else?&nbsp;Image: Whoa, mama. That is one big ass image. Will it crop out? We shall see. Also, anyway to remove the image place holder thing and just use a small camera icon or something cleaner and funner?&nbsp;Ha. He said \"funner\"And yeah, why is the first line auto H3? Let\'s figure that out.&nbsp;Alright...done for now.&nbsp;Tested on:Device: DesktopBrowser: Chrome (incognito)UpdateHit finish, and the preview was all text mashed together, no image. Probably should not show that text in the screen after you hit publish. Definitely will disorient the writer.&nbsp;</span>',8,'2015-05-22 23:18:42',8,'2015-06-05 01:34:59',2,'2015-05-22 23:18:42',8,0),(27,'c38451e1-1f2f-47eb-9b0e-295028484200','The Devil That Danced on the Water','the-devil-that-danced-on-the-water','this is a test. &nbsp;the title is working nicely.&nbsp;<div>&nbsp;this picture size is still very large. &nbsp;there was a previous iphone picture i took that said the file was too large to upload but both this one and the other one were taken from my iphone. &nbsp;&nbsp;<div><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>a double enter creates this line at the top. &nbsp;and changes the font size as i write on the desk top. &nbsp; &nbsp;when i press enter here for the next line ...&nbsp;</p><p>... it double spaces the writing between the last line and this line. &nbsp; not sure why.&nbsp;</p><p>i\'m trying the <b>highlights now. &nbsp;That seemed to work but as I continue the sentence it continues in bold. &nbsp;</b></p><h2><b>This is a test for ... OK this makes it a sub-headline but as you can see after i hit the \"h\" &nbsp;and keep writing it continues in this mode. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></h2><h2><b>Do i have to highlight again to remove this font &nbsp;size ?&nbsp;</b></h2><p>Not sure what happened but when i pressed \"h\" again which was not &nbsp;in a green highlight, it brought be back to this font size.&nbsp;</p><p>entering goes double spaced down again.&nbsp;</p><p>let me test a link : &nbsp; www.akomanet.com &nbsp; -- this was a bit confusing as it went to the top &nbsp;of the page ... i scrolled down .. and then there was a blue link line. &nbsp;but when i &nbsp;try and type after it ... &nbsp;the blue link goes away.&nbsp;</p><p>I pressed the icon of the top right with a person in it ... and decided to continue writing but the drop down menu doesnt go away. .. even when i press finish.&nbsp;</p><p>i\'ve come back into the story because everything is smushed &nbsp;when looking at the preview and there\'s no picture. &nbsp;</p><p><br></p><div><!----><p><br></p></div></div></div>','<p>this is a test. &nbsp;the title is working nicely.&nbsp;<div>&nbsp;this picture size is still very large. &nbsp;there was a previous iphone picture i took that said the file was too large to upload but both this one and the other one were taken from my iphone. &nbsp;&nbsp;<div><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>a double enter creates this line at the top. &nbsp;and changes the font size as i write on the desk top. &nbsp; &nbsp;when i press enter here for the next line ...&nbsp;</p><p>... it double spaces the writing between the last line and this line. &nbsp; not sure why.&nbsp;</p><p>i\'m trying the <b>highlights now. &nbsp;That seemed to work but as I continue the sentence it continues in bold. &nbsp;</b></p><h2><b>This is a test for ... OK this makes it a sub-headline but as you can see after i hit the \"h\" &nbsp;and keep writing it continues in this mode. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></h2><h2><b>Do i have to highlight again to remove this font &nbsp;size ?&nbsp;</b></h2><p>Not sure what happened but when i pressed \"h\" again which was not &nbsp;in a green highlight, it brought be back to this font size.&nbsp;</p><p>entering goes double spaced down again.&nbsp;</p><p>let me test a link : &nbsp; www.akomanet.com &nbsp; -- this was a bit confusing as it went to the top &nbsp;of the page ... i scrolled down .. and then there was a blue link line. &nbsp;but when i &nbsp;try and type after it ... &nbsp;the blue link goes away.&nbsp;</p><p>I pressed the icon of the top right with a person in it ... and decided to continue writing but the drop down menu doesnt go away. .. even when i press finish.&nbsp;</p><p>i\'ve come back into the story because everything is smushed &nbsp;when looking at the preview and there\'s no picture. &nbsp;</p><p><br></p><div><!----><p><br></p></div></div></div></p>','/content/images/2015/05/luka-w-water-2.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'2015-05-25 17:52:54',3,'2015-05-25 17:52:54',3,'2015-05-25 17:52:54',3,0),(29,'2b591fd2-88d2-417b-940c-e707f7aa1632','My Best Friend\'s Wedding','my-best-friends-wedding-2','I was a bridesmaid last October. It was a lot of fun but also very stressful.&nbsp;<!----><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>Here I am with my best friend Jordyn. We have known each other our<b> whole lives</b>.&nbsp;</p>','<p>I was a bridesmaid last October. It was a lot of fun but also very stressful.&nbsp;<!----><hr contenteditable=\"false\"><p>Here I am with my best friend Jordyn. We have known each other our<b> whole lives</b>.&nbsp;</p></p>','/content/images/2015/05/alannajojo.png',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,'2015-05-26 12:18:46',5,'2015-06-05 03:41:14',2,'2015-05-26 12:18:46',2,0),(48,'f42953ed-68e4-4a06-9246-76027a7889aa','Another Test of The System','another-test-of-the-system','<p>Alright...let\'s have Einstein show us how to do this thing.</p>','<p>Alright...let\'s have Einstein show us how to do this thing.</p>','/content/images/2015/06/image-4.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'2015-06-05 09:31:50',8,'2015-06-05 09:31:50',8,'2015-06-05 09:31:50',8,0),(50,'dcc0066d-1214-422a-adc8-e81fc775d47a','Test','test','<p>blah blah&nbsp;</p>','<p>blah blah&nbsp;</p>',NULL,0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'2015-06-05 23:27:20',8,'2015-06-05 23:27:20',8,'2015-06-05 23:27:20',8,0),(51,'2a04a279-4ee3-4e10-971d-98dde8782c23','this is a test from zain and is easy doing the title now. great.','this-is-a-test-from-zain-and-is-easy-doing-the-title-now-great-2','<p><br></p>','<p><br></p>','/content/images/2015/06/luka-w-water.jpg',0,0,'published','en_US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'2015-06-06 16:27:43',3,'2015-06-06 16:29:0